{"name":"Climb","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To ascend or descend sheer cliffs or walls without need of climbing gear. If vertical, the surface must be rough or cracked. At least one check must be made per 100 feet of climbing. Failure indicates the climber has slipped and fallen at about the midpoint of the check.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253059188,"modifiedTime":1681579269433,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0GuODwGkYRyach32","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Backstab","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A backstab attempt with a class 1 or 2 melee weapon. The target must be unaware of attack, which may be the result of <em>hiding</em> or <em>moving silently</em>. Also, the target must have vital organs (e.g., <strong>skeleton</strong>, <strong>zombie</strong> exempt) and a discernible &ldquo;back&rdquo; (e.g., <strong>green slime</strong>, <strong>purple worm</strong> exempt). If the requirements are met, the following benefits result:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The attack roll is made at +4 &ldquo;to hit.&rdquo;</li>\n<li>Additional weapon damage dice are rolled according to the thief&rsquo;s level of experience:\n<ul>\n<li>1st to 4th levels = &times;2</li>\n<li>5th to 8th levels = &times;3</li>\n<li>9th to 12th levels = &times;4</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Other damage modififiers (strength, sorcery, etc.) are added afterwards (e.g., a 5th-level thief with 13 strength and a <strong>+1 short sword</strong> rolls 3d6+2).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579269433,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"0XCg0IYKHdsY08bf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Agile","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+1 AC bonus when unarmoured and unencumbered (small shield allowed).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579269433,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"EdHzKzDizWJdE51Z","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Discern Noise","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To hearken at a door and detect the faintest of noises on the other side, perceive the distant footfalls of a wandering monster, or distinguish a single voice in a crowd. Six rounds (one minute) of concentrated listening are required.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253207156,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"FBpkXxeuOnfTVyNb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Detect Secret Doors","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 36\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 96\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Find a secret door on a base 3-in-6 chance.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d6","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gxkgVAngDEfiTJd7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252841676,"modifiedTime":1681579269433,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"Hth06yaatToIXi79","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Decipher Script","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To translate texts otherwise not understood. Maps can be interpreted, instructions decoded, and so forth. Ancient or alien languages, however, may remain unintelligible, lacking any basis for comparison.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253152433,"modifiedTime":1681579269433,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"Jit9sr476z9QrQBm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Dexterity","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of dexterity</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>dexterity</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"MU9Ad6GulTFsmkIb","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Read Scrolls","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke thaumaturgical (magician, magician subclasses, etc.) spell scrolls. If the attempt fails, a backfire or other unfortunate circumstance may result: A second d12 must be rolled, with a 3-in-12 chance of disaster. The spell is erased from the scroll in any event.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253348481,"modifiedTime":1681579269435,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"PNwYkJLg5958ph0z","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Hide","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To vanish into shadows, camouflage oneself, or flatten one&rsquo;s body to a seemingly impossible degree&mdash;all whilst remaining still as a statue. Only the slightest movement is permissible (e.g., unsheathing a blade, opening a pouch). Hiding is impossible in direct sunlight, or if the thief is observed.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253228973,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"XnfaAJNwkwOSinXF","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Manipulate Traps","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To find, remove, and reset traps both magical and mundane. Separate checks must be made to accomplish each facet of this skill: <em>find</em>, <em>remove</em>, <em>reset</em>. Failure by more than two, or if a natural 12 is rolled, may cause the trap to detonate on the thief. Also, a new trap may be built if the mechanism is simple and the parts available; anything more complex requires the assistance of an engineer. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required when practicing this ability.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253249264,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"eWpAEtISN93A6ryt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Pick Pockets","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To filch items from a pocket, pouch, backpack, or garment using nimble fingers and possibly distraction. Failure by a margin of 3 or greater indicates the attempt has been observed (though not necessarily by the victim). If the roll is successful, the referee must determine what has been procured. If a thief attempts to pick the pocket of a higher-level thief, legerdemainist, or purloiner, a penalty equal to the difference in levels must be applied to the check. This skill also covers the gamut of sleight-of-hand trickery a thief might employ to deceive onlookers.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":4,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253332581,"modifiedTime":1681579269435,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"oeUcattDaMrGh6qo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Move Silently","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To move with preternatural quiet, even across squeaky floorboards, dry leaves, loose debris, and the like. This skill is executed at half the thief&rsquo;s normal movement rate.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":5,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253287286,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"phCjpOOtMPXnJWM0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Progressive Thief Abilities","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The following abilities improve as the thief (and other subclasses) advances in levels of experience:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Climb</li>\n<li>Decipher script</li>\n<li>Discern noise</li>\n<li>Hide</li>\n<li>Manipulate traps</li>\n<li>Move silently</li>\n<li>Open locks</li>\n<li>Pick pockets</li>\n<li>Read scrolls</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>ATTEMPTING A PROGRESSIVE THIEF ABILITY</strong></p>\n<p>Roll a d12 to determine success or failure. If the result is equal to or less than the required number, the attempt is successful. The referee might modify the probability of success based on prevailing circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>MODIFIERS:</strong> Each ability is associated with and potentially modified by an exceptional attribute, increasing the chance-in-twelve by one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>16+ dexterity</strong> (DX): <em>climb, hide, manipulate traps, move silently, open locks,</em> and <em>pick pockets</em></li>\n<li><strong>16+ intelligence</strong> (IN): <em>decipher script</em> and <em>read scrolls</em></li>\n<li><strong style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">16+ wisdom</strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> (WS): </span><em style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">discern noise</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Examples: A 5th-level thief with 16 dexterity has an 8-in-12 chance to <em>move silently</em>. A 5th-level thief with 16 intelligence may <em>read scrolls</em> at a 1-in-12 chance of success.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>N.B.: An ability with a base ratio noted as &ldquo;&mdash;&rdquo; is not yet functional; an ability with a base ratio noted as &ldquo;0:12&rdquo; is useable only if the associated attribute (intelligence in both cases) is 16 or greater, effecting a modified 1-in-12 chance of success.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 38\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>Armour Modifier for Subclasses:</strong> <span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Subclasses with the abilities <em>climb, </em></span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><em>hide</em>, and <em>move silently</em> execute these abilities at a penalty (chance-in-twelve reduced by 4) if wearing medium armour. Executing these abilities is impossible in heavy armour.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253789343,"modifiedTime":1681579269435,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"v7DPkoXoTh8loFEu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Open Locks","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To pick locks or disable latching mechanisms both magical and mundane. Thieves&rsquo; tools are required. Picking or dismantling a lock may be attempted but once; if the attempt fails, the thief cannot try again until he has gained a level of experience. Most locks require 1d4 minutes to pick; complex locks might necessitate 3d6 minutes.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>[<strong>Table 16: Progressive Thief Abilities</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p.37]</p>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"d12","rollType":"below","rollTarget":3,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679253307994,"modifiedTime":1681579269434,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"vPLKxpx5nfuC0IFN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Thieves' Cant","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 37\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The secret language of thieves, a strange pidgin in which some words may be unintelligible to an ignorant listener, whereas others might be common yet of alternative meaning. This covert tongue is used in conjunction with specific body language, hand gestures, and facial expressions. Two major dialects of Thieves&rsquo; Cant are used in Hyperborea: one by city thieves, the other by pirates; commonalities exist betwixt the two.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"thief","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679252890133,"modifiedTime":1681579269435,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"yjuz73R1busm6CZl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
